Question: One image contains a trio of black pugs out of costume, and the other image includes no uncostumed dogs and includes at least one dog wearing a fur hood.

Reference Answer: False

Right image URL: https://i.pinimg.com/736x/7e/3d/5b/7e3d5b08aee37703daa07758ea4dbeff--road-trips-windows.jpg

Original program:

```
ANSWER0=VQA(image=LEFT,question='How many black pugs are in the image?')
ANSWER1=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='How many black pugs are in the image?')
ANSWER2=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are the pugs out of costume?')
ANSWER3=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are the pugs out of costume?')
ANSWER4=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are there any uncostumed dogs in the image?')
ANSWER5=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are there any uncostumed dogs in the image?')
ANSWER6=VQA(image=LEFT,question='Are there any dogs wearing a fur hood in the image?')
ANSWER7=VQA(image=RIGHT,question='Are there any dogs wearing a fur hood in the image?')
ANSWER8=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER0} == 3 and {ANSWER2} and not {ANSWER4}')
ANSWER9=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER1} == 0 and not {ANSWER5} and {ANSWER7}')
ANSWER10=EVAL(expr='{ANSWER8} and {ANSWER9}')
FINAL_ANSWER=RESULT(var=ANSWER10)
```
